# Variables required for github actions.  These are examples only, I recommend
# copying this somewhere safe (or to `github_variables.secret` which should be
# ignored by git and docker) and updating the values as you find them, then
# using that as a reference to set the variables for your github action.

# <-- OTHER SECRETS/VARIABLES -->
# 
#   1. Navigate to the last tab 'Settings' on your repo
#   2. go to Security->Secrets and variables->Actions
#   3. Create 'New repository secret' for these

# SSH_HOST
#
#   public host name or ip for your server

# SSH_PORT
#
#   public ssh port of your server that github action can access

# SSH_USER
#
#   user github can use to login to your server using SSH

# SSH_PRIVATE_KEY
#
#   private key github action can use to connect to your server
# 
#   On your fedora server under your home directory, run this to create
#   gh_groceries and gh_groceries.pub:
#     ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096 -f gh_groceries
#
#   Add the public key to authorized keys for your user:
#     cat gh_groceries.pub >> ~/.ssh/authorized_keys
#
#   Output the private key and copy to clipboard:
#     cat gh_groceries
